/-- `HeckeAlgebra F D r S R` is the Hecke algebra associated to the weight 2
`R`-valued automorphic forms associated to the discriminant 1 totally definite
quaternion algebra `D` over the totally real field `F`, of level `UÔéü(S)` where `S` is
a finite set of nonzero primes `v` of `­Łô× F`. To make sense of this definition we choose
a rigidification `r`, that is, a fixed `­ŁöŞ_F^Ôł×`-linear
isomorphism `D ÔŐŚ[F] ­ŁöŞ_F^Ôł× = MÔéé(­ŁöŞ_F^Ôł×)`, enabling us to define level structures and
Hecke operators `TßÁą` and `UßÁą` using 2x2 matrices.

Details: `UÔéü(S)` is the subgroup of `(D ÔŐŚ[F] ­ŁöŞ_F^Ôł×)╦ú` associated, via `r`, to the
matrices which are in `GLÔéé(­Łô×ßÁą)` for all `v Ôłë S` and which are of the form
`(a *; 0 a)` mod `v` for all `v Ôłł S`. The Hecke algebra is defined to be the
sub-`R`-algebra of the weight 2 forms of level `UÔéü(S)` generated by the following
two kinds of Hecke operators: first there are the operators
`TßÁą` associated to the matrices `(¤ľßÁą 0; 0 1)` for `v Ôłë S` (here `¤ľßÁą Ôłł ­ŁöŞ_F^Ôł×` is a local
uniformiser supported at `v`). Second, there are the Hecke operators `UßÁą,ÔéÉ`
for `v Ôłł S` and `0 Ôëá ╬▒ßÁą Ôłł ­Łô×ßÁą`, associated the matries `(╬▒ßÁą 0; 0 1)`.
These slightly nonstandard Hecke operators satisfy `UßÁą,ÔéŤ * UßÁą,Ôéť = UßÁą,ÔéŤÔéť`
and in particular this Hecke algebra is commutative (Hecke operators supported
at distinct primes commute because the decomposition of the double cosets
into single cosets can be done purely locally).
-/
def HeckeAlgebra : Type _ :=
  (Algebra.adjoin R ({T r R v | v Ôłë S} Ôł¬
  {¤ć | Ôłâ (v : HeightOneSpectrum (­Łô× F)) (_hv : v Ôłł S)
         (╬▒ : v.adicCompletionIntegers F) (h╬▒ : ╬▒ Ôëá 0), ¤ć = U r S R ╬▒ h╬▒}) :
    Subalgebra R (WeightTwoAutomorphicFormOfLevel (U1 r S) R ÔćĺÔéŚ[R]
      WeightTwoAutomorphicFormOfLevel (U1 r S) R))

namespace HeckeAlgebra

noncomputable instance instRing :
    Ring (HeckeAlgebra F D r S R) := inferInstanceAs <|
